Established in 1965, the University of Newcastle is a research-intensive university and is ranked within the world’s Top 200 Universities (QS World University Rankings 2023).
To ensure that the University is well-equipped to meet the market demand in Singapore and across the region, Newcastle Australia Institute of Higher Education (Newcastle Australia) was incorporated in Singapore in 2006 as the Asia Pacific hub of the University.
Since its establishment, Newcastle Australia has been playing an instrumental role in providing future-ready leaders with quality higher education, while undertaking collaborative research with local and regional educational institutions.
With a leading team of academics, teaching and learning staff­ based locally, students and graduates of Newcastle Australia will benefit from the University’s excellent support schemes.
To date, Newcastle Australia has graduated more than 6,000 graduates from 39 countries.
About The University Of Newcastle, Australia

A LEADING PRIVATE EDUCATION INSTITUTION IN SINGAPORE
Take courses from the University of Newcastle in Australia
at PSB Academy in Singapore and enjoy a different Asian life

As one of Singapore’s leading private education institutions with almost 60-years heritage of producing more than 200,000 learners, PSB Academy is committed to defining our identity as “Asia’s Future Academy”. Established in 1964, we started under Singapore’s Economic Development Board and later Productivity and Standards Board to upgrade the knowledge and skills of Singapore’s workforce. With an approach to education that focuses on what really matters: performance in the New Economy, PSB Academy provides quality education to shape and nurture future-ready graduates with the necessary skills and tools to stay relevant in a digitally-driven economy.

Welcome to The Newcastle Australia Institute of Higher Education (Newcastle Australia) - a campus of the University of Newcastle, Australia.

The University of Newcastle is a research-intensive University and ranked in the top 200 of the world’s universities (QS World University Rankings 2023). We are top 30 in the world for impact. Impact is measured by the Times Higher Education Impact Rankings which assess universities against the 17 United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (UN SDGs). We are ranked top 5 in the world for the SDG, partnering for a sustainable future. We are committed to solving the world's problems aligned with our core values of equity, excellence, engagement and sustainability.
The Newcastle Australia is the Asia Pacific hub of the University. We deliver highest quality programs and undertake collaborative research in partnerships with education institutions in Singapore and across the regions.
We are committed to delivering an outstanding and inspiring student experience and to ensure our graduates possess the skills, knowledge, competencies, and attitude to meet the challenges of future works.
Over the years, we have graduated more than 7,000 graduates from 39 countries, and our alumni are making meaningful and lasting contributions to businesses and wider community in Singapore and worldwide. We are proud of our role in preparing world-class graduates for Singapore and the region.
As a globally and socially committed institution, we also forge partnerships and networks for our students and staff to enable them to contribute their knowledge and expertise and to drive multidisciplinary research to address significant global issues. The Newcastle Australia will continue to play a pivotal role in leveraging the University’s excellence in research and innovation by developing mutually beneficial relationships and partnerships with the industry, public and private institutions, and the wider community.
The spirit of looking to the future to imagine and then realise possibilities is at the essence of the University of Newcastle: our motto is ‘I look ahead’.

Celebrated as one of Asia’s most advanced education, research and innovation hubs, Singapore has been the ideal location for the delivery of the University of Newcastle’s programs in the region since 2002. Our strategic location is even more relevant today with the rise of Asia.

Established as a wholly-owned entity of the University in 2006, Newcastle Australia (formerly known as UON Singapore) has continued to deliver and expand both its full-time and part-time programs. Our strong partnerships with leading local institutions provide our diverse range of local and international students access to a broad variety of professional networks when they graduate. Our researchers work with world-class organisations and institutions in the Singapore region and across the globe on research projects, research seminars and faculty-specific collaborations.

Our Mission
Newcastle Australia plays an important role in providing access to a world-class higher education in Singapore and the broader region. Newcastle Australia leverages the University of Newcastle’s academic excellence to create distinctiveness, enhance global reputation, and achieve national and regional recognition. Our education programs are respected and robust and are supported by a service culture to students. Our staff members have a range of language skills and are multi-cultural.
Newcastle Australia commits to:
Offering students the opportunity to develop a broad cultural and global perspective while pursuing an undifferentiated degree from the University of Newcastle, Australia
Nurturing future leaders of business and industry in the Asia-Pacific to drive economic and social prosperity across the region, and
Promoting and growing two-way mobility of students and staff between the University of Newcastle’s Australian and Singapore campuses
Continue your path towards a world of deeper, richer knowledge. See where our rich suite of further learning will take you.

In partnership with our university partners, we offer a suite of master’s degree programmes and MBA courses to cater to various students’ needs and career advancement.

Besides master’s degree programmes, students can also choose to take up graduate certificates or postgraduate diplomas to expand their skill-set and career opportunities.

Benefits of our master’s degree courses1 include: Full/part-time study options

Choice of 7 disciplines and 9 universities across Australia, New Zealand, the United Kingdom and the United States of America

Completion in 12 to 48 months

Conducive learning environment within City Campus near City Hall, Esplanade and Promenade MRT Stations

In 2021, almost 8 in 10 PSB Academy degree graduates were employed six months after examinations2.

Explore the world of degrees on offer from our renowned institutional partners from around the globe

In partnership with our university partners, we offer a variety of bachelor’s degree options to support your career pathways and advance your professional development in Singapore.

Benefits of our bachelor’s degree courses1 include:

Full/part-time study options

Choice of multiple disciplines to universities across Australia, the United Kingdom and the United States of America

Honours and non-honours degree options

Completion in 12 to 48 months

Second and third-year direct entry for polytechnic graduates

Conducive learning environment within City Campus near City Hall, Esplanade and Promenade MRT stations

To equip students with the relevant experience for today’s economy, some of our bachelor’s degrees offer the following benefits:

Business school accreditation by the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business (AACSB) – The University of Newcastle, Australia

Accreditation by Institution of Occupational Safety and Health (IOSH), the world’s largest professional health and safety organisation

Professional papers exemptions by Association of Chartered Certified Accountants (ACCA), Institute of Singapore Chartered Accountants (ISCA) and Institute of Chartered Accountants in England and Wales (ICAEW)

Industrial placements for The University of Newcastle, Australia’s Mechanical and Electrical and Electronic Engineering degrees

Student membership with Public Relations Institute of Australia (PRIA), the Institute of Public Relations of Singapore (IPRS), The Institution of Engineers Singapore (IES) and Singapore Computer Society (SCS)

With a series of activities and events planned by our student leaders throughout the year, embark on a holistic education journey filled with exciting activities. Check out our wide array of student clubs and be a member of our student clubs today!

Institution of Engineers Singapore (IES) is the national society of engineers in Singapore. The student chapter advances the art, science and profession of engineering, and provides a platform for engineering students in Singapore to network. Student members will gain access to “The Singapore Engineer” e-magazine, talks, workshops and industrial visits.
Google Developer Student Club PSB Academy

Supported by Google Developer and with over 1000 clubs across the globe, Google Developer Student Clubs aim to help students bridge the gap between theory and practice. Google Developer Student Club PSB Academy (DSC – PSBA) is for students interested in Google developer technologies and with interests in growing as a developer. By joining DSC- PSBA, students grow their knowledge in a peer-to-peer learning environment and build solutions for local businesses and their community.
The club paves the way for Chinese students to meet and connect through social activities like a Lunar New Year celebration with other student groups to showcase the Chinese culture.

Expect nothing less than social and cultural activities from the Indonesian students to promote mutual understanding among all students. Their schedule is packed with gatherings and sports games, all year round.
Want to embark on this exciting journey in Public Relations and Communication? Come on board now!
Leadership Development Club, a team of passionate individuals, focuses on offering opportunities for students to equip themselves with skills to be the leaders of tomorrow.
Global Student Club welcomes students from Malaysia, Vietnam, Thailand, Laos, Cambodia and many more.

A place where South Asian students can feel comfortable learning and interacting with one another while helping them feel closer to home at PSB Academy. Discover various fun activities – from welcoming the new students to celebrating Diwali.

Xin chào! If you are a Vietnamese student, look no further! Vietnamese Student Club provides a platform where Vietnamese students can come together and bond through different activities. Special occasions that celebrate the unique Vietnamese culture are also held.

Gardens by the Bay is known for its beautiful iconic Supertree grove as well as 2 greenhouse flower domes and cloud forest. With its ever-changing seasonal display, at this floral dome you can find a variety of succulents, seasonal flowers such as cherry blossoms, sunflowers, and even lavender. Supertree Grove is best visited at night, paired with a Garden Rhapsody light show and sound show. You can also head to the OCBC Skyway to walk through the woods and enjoy the view from the top.
Opening hours: 9am-9pm daily
Address: 18 Marina Gardens Drive, Singapore 018953.

Marina Barrage is one of the best places to have a picnic with family and friends! The huge grassy area on the roof is perfect for kite-flying and you can even take your pet for a walk! Bring a picnic basket and enjoy the sunset with the beautiful Singapore skyline in the background.
Address: 8 Marina Gardens Drive, Singapore 018951

This is the place to get the perfect photo. teamLAB exhibition Future World The venue for Future World: Where art and science meet. Our favorite is the 170,000 LED lights in the Crystal Universe. You'll literally feel as if you've been transported to another planet! With 21 gallery Spaces, you can explore the world of art, science, culture and technology, and the moment you step inside, you will have an immersive and breathtaking educational experience.
Opening hours: 10am to 7pm Daily
Address: 6 Bayfront Ave, Singapore 018974

For great views of Marina Bay and the Central Business District, head here! Watch the sun set over the horizon at dusk before the twinkling city lights come on.
Opening hours: 10am-10pm daily
Address: 10 Bayfront Ave, Singapore 018956

The largest Ferris wheel in Asia is definitely a must visit in Singapore. As you rise into the sky, enjoy the spectacular view of Singapore, and on a clear day you can even see Singapore Changi Airport. Fun fact: Did you know that the Singapore Flyer is as tall as 31 stacked male giraffes?
Opening hours: Thursday to Sunday 3-10pm
Address: 30 Raffles Ave, Singapore 039803
In the latest QS World University Rankings released on 28 June, the University of Newcastle, Australia has been ranked 173rd in the world out of 1500 universities.

Celebrating 21 Years of Higher Education in Singapore
Newcastle Australia celebrated a new milestone since it first established its presence in Singapore in 2002.

Our Singapore alumni network is part of a broad and vibrant community of graduates, staff, students and friends who have all shared the University of Newcastle experience. With more than 125,000 graduates across 121 countries, you can stay connected in Singapore and across the globe.

Graduates of the University of Newcastle degrees in Singapore are well taken care of by our dedicated Alumni Relations team. We are proud to have an active Singapore alumni committee fostering lifelong relationships with Newcastle Australia graduates and friends through a variety of networking opportunities. The committee organises events 'for Alumni, by Alumni' three to four times a year, and gathers our diverse group of graduates from various programs and years. These events are conducted with the aim of forging new connections, sharing industry intelligence and building stronger links to the University - all of which are supported by the University of Newcastle, Australia. With Newcastle Australia's events planned throughout the year, there are regular occasions to celebrate with your fellow Singapore alumni. We encourage you to keep in touch with your alma mater and get involved in alumni activities wherever you are across the world.

At Newcastle Australia, we believe in upholding the University of Newcastle spirit. If you would like to find out how you can be involved in any alumni activities, please contact us at: Singapore-Events@newcastle.edu.au

PSB Academy strives to ensure the wellbeing and safety of our students. We have a duty of care to provide a support system and processes to ensure our students receive the necessary support. In the event students are faced with incidents which affect their wellbeing and safety, our in-house Counsellor and staff team will provide the support, care and assistance. We will also employ peer and academic support for the student, where required. Support is also available to incidents which occur off-campus or had occurred in the past but still continue to impact the student. Students may contact our in-house Counsellor through phone or email. Tel: 6390 9214 Email: care@psb-academy.edu.sg Monday – Friday: 8:30am – 6:00pm Students may also refer to the resource referrals listed here for the 24-hr Crisis Helplines and Community Resources, based on their required needs. For incidents referred to us which require immediate medical/Police/Emergency Services assistance, we will contact the relevant authorities. We are committed to creating an inclusive environment for our students. Let us know the learning, physical, medical or mental support you need. We will do our best to help make your learning journey more accessible and flexible, even as you strive toward academic excellence.

Indicating the source of information or ideas cited or discussed in your work, as well as giving the location of quotes, is a crucial aspect of assessments.
So understanding and being able to accurately reference is a skill you need to master. But with a variety of referencing styles used, it’s can be a variety of skills.
The University has resources to help you better understand referencing, while the Library offers more in-depth information about referencing, including style guides.

What can you get out of Resources?

You can get expert advice from a Learning Advisor, or get help any time with your assignments from Library services and Studiosity. Whether it’s from your lecturers, program/course coordinators, peers or online resources, there is an abundance of support in place to help you achieve your goals. It doesn’t need to be course-specific either – you can get help with generic skills such as presentation skills.
